# BuildKit per-Dockerfile ignore for tests/e2e/Dockerfile.e2e.
#
# The root .dockerignore excludes `tests/` (correct for the production
# image), but this image's entrypoint, fixtures, and sample data live
# under tests/e2e/ — so the E2E build needs its own ignore file. When a
# `<Dockerfile-name>.dockerignore` exists, BuildKit uses it INSTEAD of
# the root .dockerignore, so this is a full copy of the root list minus
# the `tests/` line. Keep the two files in sync when editing either.
.git
.github
.venv
venv
__pycache__
*.pyc
.env
.env.*
data/
dev_data/
*.egg-info
dist/
build/
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.claude/
.idea
node_modules/
docs/
dev_docs/
infra/
server/
.dockerignore
